        "text": "Nowadays, IT and Network infrastructures are more distributed than ever before. Companies have their devices and services distributed over local networks, branch offices, customer networks (in case of MSP), data centers and in the cloud.\n\nThe IT Administrator’s wish would be to centrally monitor all distributed networks/infrastructure in one console/location. Another wish would be a monitoring solution to monitor all distributed devices and services. Paessler PRTG aims to make the life of IT Admins easier, by answering the above requirements, and a lot more.\n\nPRTG is a unified monitoring solution that will allow you to centrally monitor your local and remote infrastructure out of the box. Also for remote desktop monitoring, PRTG is the tool of your choice.\n\nUnified monitoring - one tool to monitor your local and remote networks\n\n24/ 7 monitoring through PRTG\n\nGet notified in time, hence avoiding costly downtimes\n\nCheck how your infrastructure is performing in real-time\n\nAddress bottlenecks before they cause problems\n\nPRTG Hosted Monitor\n\nYou run a PRTG Hosted Monitor instance and want to monitor your local network.\n\nSeveral locations\n\nYou have more than one location or many employees working from home and you need to ensure the availability of services from all locations.\n\nFirewalls\n\nYour network is separated in several LANs by firewalls, and the local probe cannot monitor specific services across the firewalls.\n\nSecure Connection\n\nYou want to monitor systems in a secure network, and you need a secure connection between the PRTG server and this network.\n\nDistribution of load\n\nYou need to offload the central PRTG server by taking some load and distributing it over one or more PRTG remote probes.\n\nRun PRTG on Linux\n\nYou want to run your PRTG installation in a Linux environment, for example, and use the Multi-Platform Probe feature for this purpose.\n\nMSP Solution\n\nEach product of the Paessler PRTG family can be used as a fully-featuredMSP solution. With PRTG Network Monitor, for example, you simply install the central PRTGserver in your local network and then monitor your customers’ sites via remote probes. This allows you to monitor different customers at the same time.\n\nAccess Rights\n\nMoreover, PRTG offers a credential-based system. Depending on your customers’ needs, you can define different access rights: either give them full access to their probes, groups, or sensors, so they can manage their monitoring on their own, or you just give them read-only access so that they can see their own monitoring data but not change any settings.\n\nAlerts\n\nPRTG monitors your customer’s infrastructure 24/7. You can be notified via various types of notifications (e.g. SMS, email, Pager, Push notifications) to react quickly. This alert can be sent to your customer, too. Also, escalation levels can be defined.\n\nReports\n\nYou can also create regular reports for you and for your customers, containing statistics of events, outages, uptime etc. PRTG will not only ensure you get alerted in time, it also gives you the opportunity to create easily understandable dashboards which quickly give you an overview of your local and remote sites.\n\nThinking of going to the cloud with your IT?\n\nHere is our proven roadmap\n\nThere are many questions to answer before moving your IT to the cloud, so Paessler offers\n\na free ebook that could help you.\n\nGet your free copy of our cloud ebook now."
